Sean R. Meyer

Scientist | Developer | Designer

As the Lead Engineer of Machine Learning Operations at Michigan Medicine, I oversee the deployment and maintenance of machine learning and AI models that support healthcare and medical research initiatives. My responsibilities include establishing the machine learning operations framework, which encompasses on-premise and cloud infrastructures, as well as researching novel applications of emerging technologies such as Generative AI. Additionally, I follow software development best practices to ensure robust and efficient workflows. I collaborate with data scientists, clinicians, and IT teams across the University of Michigan to maintain the reliability, efficiency, and scalability of machine learning applications in a clinical setting. Furthermore, I coordinate the design and deployment of data pipelines and model validation processes, ensuring compliance with institutional policies and industry regulations.

Experience

Lead Engineer | Machine Learning Operations, Health Information Technology & Services, Michigan Medicine | September 2022 - present

Senior Scientist | Michigan Institute for Data Science, University of Michigan | November 2021 - September 2022

Student | College of Engineering, University of Michigan | Sept 2017 - August 2021

Battle Captain | U.S. Army | July 2016 – June 2017

Business Intelligence Analyst | School of Dentistry, University of Michigan | March 2012 – July 2016

Education

PhD | Design Science | University of Michigan

MS | Design Science | University of Michigan

MBA | Business Administration, Enterprise Business Intelligence | Eastern Michigan University

BS | Computer Science | Eastern Michigan University

AAS | Interactive Web Design | Washtenaw Community College
